keyValuePair.Value: Will you make the Europa League today?
Will you make the Europa League today?
There have been plenty of twists and turns over the course of the season. But here you are, last game, and needing a win to qualify for the Europa League. Will the boys do it?
There have been plenty of twists and turns over the course of the season. But here you are, last game, and needing a win to qualify for the Europa League. Will the boys do it?
I'm confident. So are my players.
Everybody at the club knows how important Europa League qualification could be. We've fought hard all season. We're not in the mood to let it slip away from us now. We'll win!
It's up to the lads now.
The boys are desperate to be in the Europa League next season. That should be all the motivation they need today. This is a big chance for all of us. Let's make sure we take it.
We've left it late, haven't we?
I look at the players in our dressing room and, really, I wonder why it's come down to this last game. We have to win now. And then improve 100% if we want to do anything in Europe next season.
You've missed out right at the end. How low do you feel?
Your boys knew what they had to do today, but they've fallen short. You've missed out on that Europa League spot. How big a blow is this to the team?
It's about a response now.

It's when times are tough that you discover people's true characters. That definitely applies to my players. I'm waiting to see the right response from them now. That means us all being better next season.
Some of us need to think about our futures.
This is a huge disappointment for everyone connected to the club. Some of our players need to take a hard look at themselves. I'm not sure they deserve to be here next season.
We put ourselves under this pressure.
This was always going to be a difficult situation. Dropping points earlier in the season has come back to haunt us. We just couldn't handle the pressure we were under today.
Europa League is a real achievement. Happy?
Europa League is a real achievement. Happy?
The season's taken some twists and turns but today, when it really mattered, your players delivered. How important is it that you've reached the Europa League?
The season's taken some twists and turns but today, when it really mattered, your players delivered. How important is it that you've reached the Europa League?
The fans deserve this, for sure.
It's been a long season. The fans stuck with us, even when things weren't going so well. Today's a great result for our players. But it's a reward for those supporters as well.
We've done what we set out to do.
The target was always Europa League football and I'm very satisfied the players have delivered. We all know it's another step towards where we want this club to be.
It's a consolation prize, really.
I expected more from this team. We're good enough to be playing Champions League football, so this is just a small consolation, to be honest. We should be setting our sights higher, for sure.
Looking forward to next season's Europa League?
Looking forward to next season's Europa League?
A pretty dramatic finish to the season, wasn't it? Last game and you've managed to secure a Europa League spot. How big an achievement is that for your team?
A pretty dramatic finish to the season, wasn't it? Last game and you've managed to secure a Europa League spot. How big an achievement is that for your team?
That took some spirit!
We've fought hard all season long and I always thought we could do it. But, on the day, all the credit has to go to the boys. They showed some spirit, didn't they? They deserve it.
We've done what we planned to do.
Europa League was the target and we've made it. But we can't stop now. I have a long-term vision for the club. This represents just one more step on the road.
Why did we have to suffer?
We made things very difficult for ourselves. So many dropped points earlier in the season! It made for a nail-biter today. I guess I have to say I'm just pleased we made it eventually.
Do you think you're set for the Europa League?
Well it's all pretty straightforward now. After a long season, you need one point from your last game to be sure of a Europa League spot. How do you rate your chances?
%1s belong in Europe!
I know this club belongs in European competition. We have to get the result today. The club needs it and the fans deserve it. And I definitely trust my team to deliver.
It's up to the boys now.
I haven't needed to say much to the team in the build-up. They know what's at stake and the difference playing in the Europa League could make to their careers. Now they just have to deliver.
This is a last chance.
This is a last chance.

I don't feel the boys have done themselves justice. I think our team's good enough to have qualified ages ago. But, if we can make the Europa League, I suppose no-one will be bothered how we got there.

I don't feel the boys have done themselves justice. I think our team's good enough to have qualified ages ago. But, if we can make the Europa League, I suppose no-one will be bothered how we got there.
What happened to your boys today?
You looked all set for a place in the Europa League going into the game, but you failed to get the result you needed. Just how painful is it to miss out at the very last like that?
We'll respond in the right way.
The fact that we've missed out in the very last game makes it all the more difficult to come to terms with. But we'll have to go again now. The lessons are there to be learned, right?
We choked, didn't we?
We've got the ability. We had a plan for the game. But the occasion was just too big for some of the players. We can't afford to carry lads who aren't brave enough.
We won't just focus on today.
When it comes to looking back over the season, we won't just look at what happened today. We'll have to look at all the other games we dropped points in, too. Every single slip-up has cost us.
